# Schema and Seed Sync Gate

When SQLAlchemy model metadata changes (entities, columns, nullability, indexes, FKs):

- Treat schema compatibility and seed compatibility as required in the same change set.
- Do not assume `db_schema --mode migrate` applies ALTER statements; it creates missing tables and then verifies drift.
- Run an explicit strict drift check in a clean database path before finishing:
  - `python -m app.db_schema --mode recreate --env TEST --db-url <temp sqlite url>`
  - `python -m app.db_data --mode seed --env TEST --seed-profile CORE_SAMPLE --db-url <temp sqlite url>`
  - `python -m app.db_schema --mode verify --check-level strict --env TEST --db-url <temp sqlite url>`
- Add/adjust startup and CI checks when a new required reference-code family is introduced.
- If strict drift remains after `migrate`, document why and use `recreate` for local rebuild workflows.
